<span class="header1">COMMUNITY SUPPORT SERVICES</span>
<p>Leadership ability plays an important role in achieving success in this field.  Creativity and independence are valuable for those in this field as well.  If you have leadership skills and are creative, here are three occupations to consider.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Community College Administrator</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like the idea of helping others to improve their education, you may choose to become a community college administrator. In this job, you would plan educational programs for those in your community. You would also hire qualified instructors to teach them. You would need good problem solving skills.  You would also have to know how to work with large numbers of people.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Master's Degree for this job.  You also need to have a teaching certificate and experience in teaching at a community college.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A yearly salary runs from $27,000 to $90,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Reservation Agent</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BG/1216.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Reservation Agent" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a reservation agent, you would work for an airline or hotel.  You would help people reserve plane tickets and hotel rooms as they plan a vacation or business trip.  A good agent must be able to work well with people and understand the needs of travelers.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job.  You also need to be able to use a computer.  Geography and history will help you.  Many of the places that people visit are studied in these courses.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly average income of a reservation agent is $26,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Ticket Agent</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BG/43274.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Ticket Agent" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If the idea of helping people get to where they want to go appeals to you, you might become a ticket agent. As a ticket agent, you would sell tickets at bus stations, train stations, and airports. You would assign seats to passengers and check-in their luggage. You must like working with the public to be good at this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job.  You also need to know how to use a computer.  Taking Geography in high school may be a good idea. Many of the places visited by your customers are studied in this course.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The average yearly income is $26,000.</blockquote>

