<span class="header1">ART AND DESIGN</span>
<p>To do well in the occupations in this field, you need to be able to lead.  You also need to have good organization skills.  Creativity is important as well.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Museum Director</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BG/43054.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Museum Director" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A museum is a building where important relics and artifacts are kept and displayed for the public to view. The person who acquires artifacts for a museum to display and makes sure these artifacts are cared for is the museum director.  As a museum director, you would manage the staff, plan the budget, raise funds, and set museum policies. This is a very difficult job.  To succeed in it, you need plenty of energy.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A museum director usually has a Master's Degree or a Ph.D.  Work experience is also important. A director must know every part of the museum business.  Part-time jobs and entry-level positions are first steps in moving into a director's position.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $20,000 to $100,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Orchestra Conductor</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>An orchestra conductor leads a group of musicians who play different instruments.  As a conductor, you would choose the music, set up tours, and direct rehearsals and concerts. This job requires a person who has musical talent and plays an instrument well.  It also requires a person who enjoys classical music.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.  You also need to have had a successful career as a musician.  Most conductors have played in several orchestras before they gain this position.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary depends on the reputation of the orchestra the conductor directs. The salary can reach over $100,000 per year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Floral Designer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BG/43094.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Floral Designer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like flowers and plants and know how to arrange them, you might become a floral designer. As a designer, you would use different kinds of plants to make bouquets and other flower arrangements.  You would work directly with the customers, so good people skills are necessary.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Some training beyond high school may be needed.  Extracurricular activities and part-time jobs may be a way for you to get training in floral design.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary differs greatly. Some designers work for an hourly wage while others make a guaranteed salary each year. A salary of $20,000+ could be expected.</blockquote>

