<span class="header1">COMMUNICATION SERVICE</span>
<p>The processes of creating and sharing are important to each of the occupations in this field. Your creativity and communication skills are valuable assets to these occupations.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Radio Community Affairs Director</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A radio community affairs director works with a team to create public service programs to put on the radio.  These programs address a need in the community. In this job, you would learn what the community needed and plan programs that meet those needs.  To be effective in this job, you need to be a good leader and a good writer.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a college degree to become a radio community affairs director. It will be important to have experience too.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $12,000 to $40,000.  The amount depends on how much experience the director has.  It also depends on how much money the community is able to pay.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Editorial Writer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BG/43276.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Editorial Writer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like for others to know your opinions on events in your community or nation, you might become an editorial writer.  In this job, you would write an opinion about current news issues or stories.  Your goal would be to get others to agree with your point of view.  To be good at this job, you must write well.  You must also be willing to work hard to understand the issues.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a degree in journalism to work for a newspaper.  Most editorial writers work as reporters for several years.  Only then are they given the chance to write their opinions.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>An editorial writer can earn between $17,000 to $55,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Theatrical Press Agent</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A theatrical press agent handles the publicity for plays.  It is this person who lets people know when a new play opens in your city or town.  As a theatrical press agent, you would supervise the creation of posters, newspaper advertisements, and radio and television commercials.  You would also contact the newspapers, the television station, and radio stations to have the advertisements run.  This is an influential job.  Without a theatrical press agent, people would not know about the play.  No money would be made.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>To be a theatrical press agent, a college degree is needed.  An apprenticeship of three years is usually required.  You will find college courses in writing, advertising, and business to be valuable.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary for an agent is $20,000 to $75,000+.</blockquote>

